{"TopicId":211560,"ForumId":16,"TopicTitle":"Prograde marker not moving","CreatedByName":"Kerbal410","CreatedById":212401,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-01-18T01:47:57Z","PageNum":1,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"Kerbal410","CreatedById":212401,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-01-18T01:47:57Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nFor some reason, my prograde marker won\u2019t move. Please help .\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222023-01-18T01:51:05Z\u0022 title=\u002201/18/2023 01:51  AM\u0022 data-short=\u00221 yr\u0022\u003EJanuary 18, 2023\u003C/time\u003E by Kerbal410\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Vanamonde","CreatedById":27914,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-01-18T02:10:14Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWe need more details. What is happening when you expect the marker to move?\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Kerbal410","CreatedById":212401,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-01-18T02:55:39Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWhen I try the orbit tutorial, the rocket just flies vertically when I hit prograde after turning on \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Stability Augmentation System\u0022\u003ESAS\u003C/abbr\u003E. Flying with out it is worse, as I don\u2019t know when to start turning. any mod out there that can cause this, or perhaps fix it?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Leganeski","CreatedById":220954,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-01-18T04:25:49Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nDid you set the navball to orbit mode? If you don\u0027t, it will calculate prograde as surface prograde, which doesn\u0027t deviate from vertical until after you start turning.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Kerbal410","CreatedById":212401,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-01-18T21:43:56Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224220975\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022211560\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221674015949\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022220954\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Leganeski\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n17 hours ago, Leganeski said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nDid you set the navball to orbit mode? If you don\u0027t, it will calculate prograde as surface prograde, which doesn\u0027t deviate from vertical until after you start turning.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI\u2019ll try that, thanks!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Kerbal410","CreatedById":212401,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-01-18T23:29:39Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nhang on. any way I can more/less have it fly for me, like in the \u0022go for orbit!\u0022 tutorial? Also found out that target was what I was looking for in the tutorial.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222023-01-18T23:47:33Z\u0022 title=\u002201/18/2023 11:47  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00221 yr\u0022\u003EJanuary 18, 2023\u003C/time\u003E by Kerbal410\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"linuxgurugamer","CreatedById":129964,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-01-19T01:08:06Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224221325\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022211560\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221674084579\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022212401\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Kerbal410\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n1 hour ago, Kerbal410 said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nhang on. any way I can more/less have it fly for me, like in the \u0022go for orbit!\u0022 tutorial? Also found out that target was what I was looking for in the tutorial.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYou would need an autopilot mod, such as Mechjeb, or Gravity Turn\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"}]}